In the computation above the absolute value was superfluous since the
angular velocity was positive. However if the object were traveling
clockwise it would have been essential to take the absolute value
first because a negative speed is meaningless.
</p>
            
<aside>
<title>Terminology</title>
<p>
In ordinary speech the words speed and velocity are often used
interchangeably, which can make the distinction we are stressing here
difficult to absorb. The distinction is this: Velocity has a magnitude
and a direction. The magnitude of velocity is speed.
</p>
</aside>

