<p>
The <q>co</q> prefix in front of the other trig functions is an
abbreviation of the the word <q>complement</q>. The six
<term>trigonometric functions</term> are thus the sine (<m>\sin</m>), cosine
(<m>\cos</m>), tangent (<m>\tan</m>), cotangent (<m>\cot</m>), secant (<m>\sec</m>), and
cosecant (<m>\csc</m>).
</p>

