It would be difficult to express the cycloid as the graph of some
curve: <m>y=y(x)</m>. But it is fairly simple to parameterize it, as we
will see in <xref ref="PROBLEMcycloid2">Problem~\</xref>. In our parameterization
<m>\theta</m> will still represent an angle but this time the vertex of the
angle is at the center of the wheel, which is in motion. This makes
the parameterization a little more interesting\aside{Often,
  <q>interesting</q> also means <q>more challenging.</q> }.  The placement
of <m>\theta</m> is shown schematically in the next problem.
</p>


