<subsection>
<title>Spin Casting, Redux</title>
<p>
In <xref ref="SUBSECTIONParametricFunctions">Section</xref> we saw how Newton<rsq/>s fluxional
approach to Calculus led us naturally to the notion of parametric
equations, <m> P(t)=\ParamEqThree { x=x(t)} { y=y(t)} { a\lt t \lt b}
</m>.
</p>

<!-- <figure> -->
<!-- <caption> -->
<!-- <url href="https://mathshistory.st-andrews.ac.uk/Biographies/Hooke/" visual="https://mathshistory.st-andrews.ac.uk/Biographies/Hooke/">This figure needs a caption.</url> -->
<!-- </caption> -->
<!-- </figure> -->
<!-- \begin{wrapfigure}[13]{r}{2in} -->
