<p>
To find the differential of <m>\arcsec(x)</m> we refer to the sketch
above and we proceed exactly as before. If <m>y=\arcsec(x)</m>, then
<m>x=\sec(y)</m> so
<md>
<mrow> \dx{(\sec(y))} \amp =\dx{x}</mrow>
<mrow>\sec(y)\tan(y)\dx{y}\amp = \dx{x}</mrow>
</md>
so that <me> \dx{y} =\frac{{1}}{\sec(y)\tan(y)}\dx{x}.</me>
</p>

