<p>
To see this recall  <xref ref="FIGURECurvature"></xref>. If we suppose that <m>\abs{\dfdx{\theta}{s}}=\kappa</m> then
we see that <me>\dfdx{\theta}{s}=\pm\kappa</me> and that
<md>
<mrow>\sin(\theta)\amp{}=\dfdx{y}{s} \amp{}\amp{}\text{ and } \amp{}\amp{}
\cos(\theta)=\dfdx{x}{s}.</mrow>
</md>
</p>

